{"overview":"A bright, diatonic A major piece in 6/8 whose harmonic language is deliberately simple and stable, built almost entirely on I, IV, and V with smooth diatonic pivots to the dominant key of E major and back; its most distinctive feature is the symmetrical binary-leaning form where a lyrical, grace-note-inflected A-section theme returns expanded and texturally enriched after a contrasting ornamental B section, creating an intimate, song-like arc.","cross_piece_tags":["binary","lyrical","intimate","meditative","circle_of_fifths","arpeggiated_bass"]}
